1) registerTool:

server.registerTool(
  "inventory_lookup",
  {
    title: "Inventory lookup",
    description: "List products whose stock is below the given threshold.",
    inputSchema: { below: z.number().int().min(0).default(25) },
  },
  async ({ below }) => {
    const rows = db.prepare(
      `SELECT name AS product, stock, reorder_level
       FROM products WHERE stock < ? ORDER BY stock ASC`
    ).all(below);
    return { content: [{ type: "text", text: JSON.stringify(rows, null, 2) }] };
  }
);

2) SQL run by the handler:

SELECT name AS product, stock, reorder_level
FROM products WHERE stock < ? ORDER BY stock ASC

Why it grants no new access: the agent still can only send a tools/call for inventory_lookup with a single validated `below` argument — the server writes and runs the SQL and owns the read-only DB connection, so the agent's reach is exactly the tools you chose to expose and nothing more.
